My example call

-g=/Users/paulhager/Documents/BachelorArbeit/KNIME_Node/geneRegionsTest.bed -f=/Users/paulhager/Documents/BachelorArbeit/KNIME_Node/filtMinTest.txt -a=/Users/paulhager/Documents/BachelorArbeit/KNIME_Node/SL154375.variant_filtered.trio.vcf.gz -r=/Users/paulhager/Documents/BachelorArbeit/KNIME_Node/HMNNHCCXX_s1_1_GSLv3-7_49_SL154375.filtered.fastq_mem.sorted.mergedAll.realigned.recal.CHR1_CHR2_4Mil.sort.bam,/Users/paulhager/Documents/BachelorArbeit/KNIME_Node/rnanz1_1-2_S13_R1_001_val_1.fq.Aligned.out.CHR1_CHR2_4Mil.sort.bam -m=60,255 -p=SL154375 -t -d=/Users/paulhager/Documents/BachelorArbeit/KNIME_Node/testPED.ped -c=/Users/paulhager/Documents/BachelorArbeit/KNIME_Node/chromFa/chr1.fa -o=/Users/paulhager/Documents/BachelorArbeit/KNIME_Node/smartPhaseOutput.txt

REQUIRED
-g -> genomic regions bed file. An example file using canonical genes from UCSC table browser is included

-f -> filtered variants to be analyzed for compound heterozygosity. Can be vcf or pulled from gemini. Must be tab seperated. 
		First column is contig. Second column is var start. Third column is var end (if not vcf). Fourth column is ref allele. Fifth column is nonref alleles (comma seperated)

-a -> vcf file containing all variants

-r -> all read files to be analyzed. Comma seperated paths. Requires at least one file

-m -> minimum mapping quality for each read file provided. Must be given as comma seperated list in same order as read files

-p -> patient ID

-o -> output file


OPTIONAL
-t -> flag indicating trio information is available

-d -> path to pedigree file specifying familial relationship to be used for trio phasing